Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks Report: Guaranty Trust Bank; NIC Bank Are Active

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-08-18T16:01:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-guaranty-trust-bank-nic-bank-move.html
Namibia’s FTSE/ Namibia Overall Index (FTN098) 
slumped 3.7 percent to 754.67 by the 4 p.m. close in the capital
Windhoek, the biggest drop since May 7, 2010.  Kenya’s All-Share Index jumped 0.9 percent to 62.70 by the
3 p.m. close in Nairobi, the biggest closing gain since April 5.
Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index declined for a second day, retreating
0.2 percent to 1,944.72 by the 1:30 p.m. close in  Port Louis .
The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index rose for a third
day, advancing less than 0.1 percent to 22,828.33 by the 2:30
p.m. end of trading in Lagos, according to a statement on the
bourse’s website. The Ghana Stock Exchange Composite Index fell
for the first day in three, weakening less than 0.1 percent to
1,178.32 by the 3 p.m. close in Accra.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.        Guaranty Trust Bank Plc (GUARANTY)  ,  Nigeria ’s second-
biggest lender by market value, gained 5 kobo, or 0.4 percent,
to 13.16 naira, the highest close since Aug. 5, after saying it
was on course to achieving a loan growth rate of as much as 15
percent this year.  NIC Bank Ltd. (NICB)  , a Kenyan lender, rose for a second
day, gaining 75 cents, or 2.3 percent, to 33.5 shillings, after
the Nairobi-based bank said first-half profit jumped 34 percent
as earnings from loans increased.  To contact the reporter on this story:
